scene.message:
Nanjo: The selection here{nl}
is utterly lacking...{nl}
The library at my estate{nl}
puts this to shame.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: What do you even want{nl}
in the library? C'mon,{nl}
let's go visit — er, get{nl}
that checkup!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Those two in the{nl}
corner are making fun of{nl}
Devil Boy, apparently.{waitkey}{clearbox}Personally, I think Devil Boy{nl}
beats any stuck-up snob{nl}
who acts like they're{nl}
better than everyone.{waitkey}{ret}

Kuroori: ...Oh, it's {ctl0f:1}.{nl}
Heh heh heh. I'm looking{nl}
into the school's{nl}
7 mysteries right now.{waitkey}{clearbox}Want me to tell you?{nl}
Heh heh heh.{nl}
...Later.{waitkey}{ret}

{color:2}Kuroori Tsutomu.{nl}
Nickname: "Devil Boy."{nl}
An occult fanatic —{nl}
though often quite wrong.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Student: They call him{nl}
"Devil Boy," but he's off{nl}
base about everything.{waitkey}{clearbox}My occult knowledge is{nl}
miles ahead of his.{nl}
Not that I'd share it{nl}
with an amateur.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: Even demons must{nl}
have their friendships and{nl}
their feuds, I suppose.{waitkey}{clearbox}If two enemies happened to{nl}
cross paths... that could{nl}
get pretty ugly,{nl}
couldn't it?{waitkey}{ret}

Student: See that Devil Boy{nl}
over there? He fell again{nl}
in PE today.{waitkey}{clearbox}Everyone cracked up.{nl}
He can't do a single{nl}
push-up! Can you believe it?{nl}
Poor guy!{waitkey}{ret}
